  "web3_meme_trade_config_gas_dialog_title": "What is network fee？",
  "web3_meme_trade_config_gas_dialog_definition_content": "Network fee is transaction costs paid for executing trades or contract operations on the EVM network. Adjusting network fee can change transaction priority-the higher the fee, the faster the confirmation, but at a higher cost. (Note: Gwei is the smallest unit of ETH, where 1 Gwei = 0.000000001 ETH.)",
  "web3_meme_trade_config_gas_dialog_suggestion_content": "During high market volatility or trading volume, increasing the gas fee by 10%-20% can help speed up transaction confirmation, especially for large trades or when buying trending assets.",
  "web3_meme_trade_config_priority_dialog_title": "What is priority fee？",
  "web3_meme_trade_config_priority_dialog_definition_content": "Priority fee is additional fee paid by users to expedite transaction processing. During network congestion, they incentivize miners or validators to prioritize the transaction, speeding up confirmation. Priority fee is deducted even if the transaction fails.",
